Twenty-four Limpopo young people who died in a horrific accident last Sunday when their overloaded Taxi collided head-on with a bus have been buried today in their respective village around Bolobedu. Twenty-one of them were buried in a mass funeral service held at Ga-Rapitsi sports ground outside Tzaneen. The mass funeral service was attended by top government officials including Transport Minister. Dekeledi Magadza the Deputy Minister of Transport, Fikile Mbalula Minister of Transport and Limpopo Premier Stan Mathabatha.